SIMPLE: colliquation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Colliquation
<hw>Col`li*qua"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
melting together; the act of melting; fusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When sand and ashes are well melted together and suffered to cool,
there is generated, by the <qex>colliquation</qex>, that sort of
concretion we call ⟦ldquo⟧glass⟦rdquo⟧.</q>
<rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A processive wasting or melting
away of the solid parts of the animal system with copious excretions of
liquids by one or more passages.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Colliquative</ent>⟦br⟧
